\end{proof}

\begin{proof}
    Consider the projectivized tautological bundle $\calS \to \Gr(r,W)$. The action of $G$ on $ \bbP W$ extends to $\Gr(r,W)$ and diagonally to $\calS$. 

    Let $\calG = \bar{G \cdot \pi_{\Gr}^{-1}(E)}$. Since $F$ is in the orbit-closure of $E$ in the Grassmannian, it follows by the definition of the product topology that for any $S \in F$, the point $(F, [S])$ must be in the orbit-closure of the set of all points $(E, [T])$ where $T \in E$. 

    Because $(F, [S])$ is in the orbit-closure of the fiber over $E$, and the projection $\pi_W$ is continuous, the image $\pi_W(F, [S]) = [S]$ must be in the orbit-closure of the image $\pi_W(E, [T]) = [T]$. Thus, $S$ is a degeneration of $T$ for every $T \in E$.
\end{proof}

